    "new_prompt_text": "Write a complete, high-performance, and self-contained Python script that reads the problem instance from standard input (stdin) and solves it. The script must implement an efficient optimization algorithm (e.g., Dijkstra, DP, or a heuristic search) to minimize the total cost for the target set provided via stdin. \n\nCRITICAL: Do not mention that the input data is missing. Do not provide a theoretical explanation. Do not provide a framework. Provide only a fully functional script that is ready to be executed against a standard input stream. The script must output the result in the following format:\nFINAL_ANSWER: <answer>\nJUSTIFICATION: <brief justification>\n\nReturn exactly one JSON object in this format:\n{\n  \"schema_name\": \"eywa_node_response\",\n  \"schema_version\": \"v1\",\n  \"orchestration_decision\": \"execute_locally\",\n  \"decision_notes\": \"optional string\",\n  \"response\": \"FINAL_ANSWER: <answer>\\nJUSTIFICATION: <brief justification>\",\n  \"result_type\": \"summary\"\n}"
  },
